<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="516" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1115/3961: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in
                            France</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-16T19:00:00-04:00">August 16, 1937—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>B–285. In view of the information in your August 15, 1 p.m., and since
                            the <hi rend="italic">Kane</hi> probably cannot in any event accommodate
                            all the Cuban refugees at Gijon, it is suggested that preference in
                            evacuation be given to women and children and to men with families.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>